BOOK TWO The Education of a Personage CHAPTER The Supercilious Sacrifice ATLANTIC CITY . 
Amory paced the board walk at day's end , lulled by the everlasting surge of changing waves , smelling the half mournful odor of the salt breeze . 
The sea , he thought , had treasured its memories deeper than the faithless land . 
WellAmory Blaine ! Amory looked down into the street below . 
