He was in an eddy again , a deep , lethargic gulf , without desire to work or write , love or dissipate . 
For the first time in his life he rather longed for death to roll over his generation , obliterating their petty fevers and struggles and exultations . 
His youth seemed never so vanished as now in the contrast between the utter loneliness of this visit and that riotous , joyful party of four years before . 
To hold a man a woman has to appeal to the worst in him . 
This sentence was the thesis of most of his bad nights , of which he felt this was to be one . 
His mind had already started to play variations on the subject . 
In his room he undressed and wrapping himself in blankets to keep out the chill October air drowsed in an armchair by the open window . 
He felt that life had rejected him . 
